    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, AND FENDERS - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, AND
        9400 - ADJUSTMENTS - REAR HOOD LOCATOR BLOCK
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR HOOD LOCATOR BLOCK</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>9200 (Before July 1996) - Rear Hood Locator Block Adjustment Up or Down</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900189">Figure 89</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses, unless otherwise stated.
            </para>
            <para>To adjust the hood up or down (Item 9) at the rear hood locator block (Item 7) to align the top of the
                hood with the cowl, use the following procedure.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly enough to
                    adjust the rear hood locator block (Item 7).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen, but do not remove, the adjustment bolts (Item 10) that secure the rear hood
                    locator block (Item 7) to the inside of the hood. Adjust the rear hood locator block up or down
                    (Item 9) on the slotted holes to raise or lower the hood, as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the rear hood locator block (Item 7) in place and tighten adjustment bolts (Item
                    10).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat this procedure for the other side.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the hood to the closed position and latch the hood on each side. Check to see that
                    the top of the hood is the same height as the cowl (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900190">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If further adjustment is required, repeat this procedure.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900189" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001C9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. 9200 Hood Locator Block</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REAR EDGE OF HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD LATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. REAR HOOD LOCATOR SUPPORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CAB</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HOOD LOCATOR BLOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. ADJUSTMENT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. ADJUST IN DIRECTION OF ARROW UP OR DOWN</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. ADJUSTMENT BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900190" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001D0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Top of Hood Same Height as Cowl</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
